1
00:00:10,633 --> 00:00:11,700
<i> I'll triple it!</i>

2
00:00:11,833 --> 00:00:14,133
<i>Whatever Amo gave you,
I'll triple it.</i>

3
00:00:14,267 --> 00:00:15,033
<i> In exchange for what?</i>

4
00:00:15,167 --> 00:00:17,233
<i>Tell me everything Amo told you
to do.</i>

5
00:00:17,367 --> 00:00:18,667
<i>I'm already at the targets
house.</i>

6
00:00:18,800 --> 00:00:20,900
<i>Just don't move until
that police girl gets there.</i>

7
00:00:21,033 --> 00:00:23,267
<i>Stop giving my mother flowers,
okay?</i>

8
00:00:23,400 --> 00:00:25,867
<i>Marissa Conde,
five months pregnant.</i>

9
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:27,200
<i> Same last name as Sir Tonyo's?</i>

10
00:00:27,333 --> 00:00:28,800
<i>But why are you confessing now?</i>

11
00:00:28,933 --> 00:00:30,867
<i>Think carefully about whether
you're going to vote</i>

12
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,500
<i>for Amo If all he's doing
is lying to win.</i>

13
00:00:34,667 --> 00:00:36,000
<i> You're a bunch of jerks!</i>

14
00:00:36,133 --> 00:00:38,033
<i>Amo is your father, right, Sir?</i>

15
00:00:42,233 --> 00:00:43,933
Why didn't you tell me that the
person of interest

16
00:00:44,067 --> 00:00:46,267
in the cases we're investigating
is your father?

17
00:00:50,900 --> 00:00:52,067
I thought you were a police
officer.

18
00:00:53,200 --> 00:00:54,733
You're a showbiz insider too.

19
00:00:56,300 --> 00:00:58,100
Why can't you answer
my questions?

20
00:01:01,767 --> 00:01:04,733
Because he has nothing to do
with my work, Enriquez.

21
00:01:05,233 --> 00:01:06,200
Is he really nothing,

22
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:08,667
or are you just protecting him
because he's your father?

23
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:10,733
Be careful with what you say.

24
00:01:13,200 --> 00:01:16,400
If you want to waste time
on gossip,

25
00:01:17,867 --> 00:01:18,867
don't involve me in it.

26
00:01:20,333 --> 00:01:21,500
I still have work to do.

27
00:01:56,267 --> 00:01:57,033
Hi, Doc.

28
00:01:59,033 --> 00:02:00,033
You're hardworking.

29
00:02:00,333 --> 00:02:01,367
Lieutenant Garcia.

30
00:02:02,433 --> 00:02:04,000
What are you doing here?

31
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:07,400
Didn't you say you missed me
yesterday?

32
00:02:07,933 --> 00:02:12,500
And I came here so you wouldn't
miss me anymore.

33
00:02:13,100 --> 00:02:14,700
Besides, I'll get the report
anyway.

34
00:02:15,033 --> 00:02:18,000
Did you know I found a bullet
in Bullet's brain?

35
00:02:18,900 --> 00:02:20,900
And that's been there
more or less,

36
00:02:21,267 --> 00:02:22,500
for about 10 years.

37
00:02:22,833 --> 00:02:23,833
It's been a while.

38
00:02:24,700 --> 00:02:27,967
But you know, that's a big help
in our investigation.

39
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,533
Did you get the bullet
in the brain

40
00:02:31,133 --> 00:02:35,200
so we can do a ballistic
examination

41
00:02:35,333 --> 00:02:38,500
and cross-reference it
with our database?

42
00:02:38,633 --> 00:02:40,900
Next time, after the autopsy.

43
00:02:41,033 --> 00:02:43,833
We might find another bullet
in his body.

44
00:02:45,067 --> 00:02:46,033
Okay, I'll go ahead.

45
00:02:50,167 --> 00:02:51,900
That Doctor is a sadist too.

46
00:02:52,033 --> 00:02:53,967
She prefers to miss me.

47
00:02:58,533 --> 00:03:01,533
Conde, how's Bullet's house?

48
00:03:03,700 --> 00:03:07,033
So far, Sir, we haven't found
any leads at Bullet's house.

49
00:03:08,933 --> 00:03:09,567
Garcia,

50
00:03:10,733 --> 00:03:12,267
how's Doctor Cecilia?

51
00:03:14,033 --> 00:03:14,600
Sir?

52
00:03:14,733 --> 00:03:16,333
Doc Cecilia, how's she?

53
00:03:18,133 --> 00:03:20,433
We're getting stronger.

54
00:03:22,567 --> 00:03:26,867
Well, we're getting
a little better.

55
00:03:27,167 --> 00:03:33,067
Actually, I have a plan to make
her something, baklava.

56
00:03:33,533 --> 00:03:35,133
Try that, Sir. That's delicious.

57
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:40,900
Then maybe from there,
only God knows what happens.

58
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:42,900
Garcia!

59
00:03:44,667 --> 00:03:45,833
What are you talking about?

60
00:03:45,967 --> 00:03:49,100
What I'm talking about is the
bullet found in Bullet's body!

61
00:03:51,933 --> 00:03:52,867
Is that it?

62
00:03:53,267 --> 00:03:56,767
I thought you were asking
how Doc and I were.

63
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:03,300
Doc told me, she said she'd text
me when there's an update.

64
00:04:04,100 --> 00:04:07,967
But for now, she's preparing
for the autopsy.

65
00:04:08,100 --> 00:04:11,600
Maybe they'll find another
bullet in Bullet's body.

66
00:04:13,033 --> 00:04:14,633
You and Doc Cecilia seem close.

67
00:04:15,867 --> 00:04:17,767
Please tell her
to speed up the processing

68
00:04:17,900 --> 00:04:18,767
of the bullet's ballistics

69
00:04:18,900 --> 00:04:21,233
and maybe we'll stumble upon
a lead there.

70
00:04:22,200 --> 00:04:24,467
Sure, Bok. Is that all?
We're close.

71
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:26,233
Conde,

72
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:28,967
where is Enriquez?

73
00:04:31,467 --> 00:04:35,533
Grandmother, all I'm looking
for is transparency.

74
00:04:35,667 --> 00:04:37,600
Is that too much,
Grandmother?

75
00:04:37,733 --> 00:04:40,233
My God, Grandmother,
that's so basic.

76
00:04:41,100 --> 00:04:44,000
Especially if the person of
interest is the person involved.

77
00:04:44,133 --> 00:04:45,500
Did he admit it?

78
00:04:45,633 --> 00:04:46,900
Not directly.

79
00:04:47,200 --> 00:04:50,200
But it seems like
that's how it is.

80
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:52,467
How can I not doubt him?

81
00:04:52,600 --> 00:04:55,267
Every time I ask him,
he avoids me.

82
00:04:56,233 --> 00:04:59,100
Grandmother,
I know he has a personal issue,

83
00:04:59,733 --> 00:05:02,900
but this case is very important.

84
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:06,833
Maybe you have a personal issue
with Tonyo.

85
00:05:07,767 --> 00:05:12,100
Grandmother, my only issue
with Tonyo is his father,

86
00:05:12,233 --> 00:05:13,267
nothing else.

87
00:05:13,567 --> 00:05:15,767
Maybe you want him
to feel guilty,

88
00:05:15,900 --> 00:05:18,200
so you have a reason
to not like him

89
00:05:18,333 --> 00:05:21,400
because you're starting
to like him.

90
00:05:21,733 --> 00:05:24,467
Come on, Grandmother,
I don't like him!

91
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:27,767
All I want is for us
to solve this case.

92
00:05:29,167 --> 00:05:30,067
That's all.

93
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,200
Chief, can I ask a question?

94
00:05:36,967 --> 00:05:42,933
Do we really need to investigate
Victor Santiago?

95
00:05:43,067 --> 00:05:48,200
You know, Garcia, in a way,
we're already investigating him.

96
00:05:49,533 --> 00:05:54,400
But Sir, what Selena says about
Victor being the mastermind

97
00:05:54,533 --> 00:05:55,400
of Sonny and Bullet is
meaningless

98
00:05:55,533 --> 00:05:57,867
if we can't back it up
with solid evidence.

99
00:05:58,600 --> 00:06:01,567
The sniper,
is there any news about him?

100
00:06:01,700 --> 00:06:02,500
Nothing yet, Sir.

101
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:05,067
But I'm sure he's not far away,

102
00:06:06,033 --> 00:06:07,900
especially since his mission
isn't over yet.

103
00:06:29,933 --> 00:06:30,900
Where am I?

104
00:06:31,333 --> 00:06:32,267
It's okay, Woo.

105
00:06:32,933 --> 00:06:33,967
Everything's fine.

106
00:06:35,767 --> 00:06:37,933
Woo, I'm disappointed.

107
00:06:38,667 --> 00:06:41,033
Selena, she's still alive.

108
00:06:41,433 --> 00:06:43,433
She will die soon.

109
00:06:43,967 --> 00:06:46,933
And two civilians were able
to identify your face.

110
00:06:47,467 --> 00:06:48,533
It doesn't matter.

111
00:06:49,500 --> 00:06:52,100
I've experienced worse in other
countries.

112
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:53,400
But you know what?

113
00:06:54,167 --> 00:06:56,700
Nobody catches me.

114
00:06:58,500 --> 00:07:00,033
I'll finish my job.

115
00:07:00,267 --> 00:07:02,133
Just get the money ready
when I'm done.

116
00:07:04,267 --> 00:07:05,567
Well, at least, half of it.

117
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:09,100
I just gave half of your pay
to another hitman

118
00:07:09,467 --> 00:07:10,700
to clean up your mess.

119
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:12,900
Hey, can you blame me?

120
00:07:17,833 --> 00:07:20,600
What we can look at, Sir,
is Daga's angle.

121
00:07:20,733 --> 00:07:21,367
Daga?

122
00:07:22,433 --> 00:07:23,333
What do you mean?

123
00:07:24,267 --> 00:07:27,667
Because if his exposé about
Victor Santiago is true.

124
00:07:28,300 --> 00:07:30,400
Technically,
he's Victor's henchman,

125
00:07:30,767 --> 00:07:34,267
just like Sonny and Bullet,
if we believe Selena.

126
00:07:34,500 --> 00:07:35,467
Why, Bok?

127
00:07:35,700 --> 00:07:37,833
Do you think Daga knows anything
about Sonny and Victor?

128
00:07:38,367 --> 00:07:41,633
We'll find out when we talk
to Daga.

129
00:07:43,767 --> 00:07:47,767
Amo, I have an initial pool
of top lawyers that we can get

130
00:07:47,933 --> 00:07:49,100
for the prosecution.

131
00:07:49,233 --> 00:07:50,333
Prosecution?

132
00:07:50,967 --> 00:07:54,933
As of now, Amo, our best course
of action for Daga's exposé

133
00:07:55,067 --> 00:07:56,967
is to actually file a case.

134
00:07:57,633 --> 00:08:00,133
Besides, he won't be able
to prove that you paid him.

135
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,900
What, will you check the names,
Amo?

136
00:08:03,500 --> 00:08:04,600
Go with your guts.

137
00:08:04,933 --> 00:08:06,367
I'm trusting you on this, okay.

138
00:08:07,033 --> 00:08:07,833
Copy, Amo.

139
00:08:09,067 --> 00:08:11,200
There's nothing to worry about,
Amo.

140
00:08:11,467 --> 00:08:12,667
You'll get through this.

141
00:08:13,033 --> 00:08:14,433
I'm just thinking...

142
00:08:15,300 --> 00:08:17,500
If Joaquin wants to play dirty,

143
00:08:19,300 --> 00:08:20,833
I'll give him that.

144
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:26,267
And where do you think you're
going?

145
00:08:27,567 --> 00:08:28,633
I already told you.

146
00:08:28,767 --> 00:08:30,200
Just get the money ready.

147
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:31,733
Are you deaf Woo?

148
00:08:32,067 --> 00:08:34,867
I just told you you've been
compromised.

149
00:08:35,867 --> 00:08:37,367
How are you going to finish
your work?

150
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:41,267
I don't give out free trade
secrets.

151
00:08:43,300 --> 00:08:44,067
Trade secrets?

152
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:46,867
Stop, okay? Just stop.

153
00:08:47,900 --> 00:08:48,833
I already told you.

154
00:08:49,667 --> 00:08:52,633
I already sent a hitman to take
care of the two witnesses.

155
00:08:52,867 --> 00:08:55,300
And besides, we have no idea
where Selena is.

156
00:08:55,633 --> 00:08:56,667
We know nothing,

157
00:08:56,900 --> 00:08:59,633
so how can you finish your work
without knowing anything?

158
00:08:59,767 --> 00:09:01,500
We know nothing.

159
00:09:02,533 --> 00:09:03,633
Let's see.

160
00:09:06,467 --> 00:09:08,200
Are Koreans really stubborn?

161
00:09:09,700 --> 00:09:10,967
You know, after what happened,

162
00:09:11,233 --> 00:09:13,367
Godfather's ratings
are definitely going to drop.

163
00:09:15,233 --> 00:09:16,133
It should.

164
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:17,800
He had it coming.

165
00:09:18,133 --> 00:09:21,667
Well, it's nice to see good
journalism at work.

166
00:09:22,967 --> 00:09:26,600
There is no stench
that is not revealed.

167
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:32,600
Daddy, did Uncle Victor really
do what's on social media?

168
00:09:33,433 --> 00:09:36,867
That he paid those people
to make him look like a hero?

169
00:09:38,633 --> 00:09:39,833
What do you think, Faye?

170
00:09:43,067 --> 00:09:45,767
I don't know, Mommy, because it
seems like this only happens

171
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:47,967
in movies or drama shows.

172
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:52,267
Actually, Faye,
even I was surprised.

173
00:09:53,167 --> 00:09:54,000
Me too.

174
00:09:55,267 --> 00:09:58,833
I don't know what else Victor
will do to defeat me.

175
00:10:00,000 --> 00:10:00,967
It's sad.

176
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:05,833
Dude.

177
00:10:10,067 --> 00:10:12,400
This Faye Guerrero is really
a winner.

178
00:10:12,667 --> 00:10:13,467
She's beautiful, isn't she?

179
00:10:14,833 --> 00:10:17,733
The question is, when will our
buddy wake up?

180
00:10:18,433 --> 00:10:19,333
What do you mean wake up?

181
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,733
Dude, think about it.

182
00:10:20,867 --> 00:10:23,200
You know I've always wanted
a sports car for a long time,

183
00:10:23,333 --> 00:10:25,400
but have you ever seen me drool
over it?

184
00:10:25,833 --> 00:10:27,867
No, because I know I can never
have one.

185
00:10:28,900 --> 00:10:31,333
Dude, don't believe him.

186
00:10:31,467 --> 00:10:34,600
Hey Bal, that's because
you're a weakling.

187
00:10:34,767 --> 00:10:38,667
Because you can't reach
the stars in heaven,

188
00:10:39,200 --> 00:10:40,167
because you're the devil.

189
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:41,367
Bars!

190
00:10:42,700 --> 00:10:45,533
You know, leave him alone, man.
That's because no one likes you.

191
00:10:45,667 --> 00:10:46,367
What's with you?

192
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,400
Every day is my anniversary,
hey.

193
00:10:47,533 --> 00:10:49,867
-What every day?
- Anniversary? Maybe it's death.

194
00:10:51,767 --> 00:10:53,000
What are you doing here?

195
00:10:53,300 --> 00:10:55,133
It's like you're not doing
anything here.

196
00:10:55,267 --> 00:10:56,833
Perfect timing, Bro.

197
00:10:57,133 --> 00:10:58,833
Mar, Abdul, maybe we could,
what...

198
00:10:58,967 --> 00:11:01,033
You know. We're your bodyguards,
of course, right?

199
00:11:01,167 --> 00:11:02,100
- Bodyguard!
- Right!

200
00:11:02,233 --> 00:11:03,500
Talent fee, maybe.

201
00:11:03,633 --> 00:11:06,633
Maybe you could give us at least
six months down payment

202
00:11:06,767 --> 00:11:07,667
so we can be motivated.

203
00:11:07,800 --> 00:11:08,900
Six months advance?

204
00:11:09,733 --> 00:11:11,233
You're not doing anything.

205
00:11:11,567 --> 00:11:12,500
Look at this,
he's just watching reels.

206
00:11:12,633 --> 00:11:14,133
- Watching a girl.
- Let me see.

207
00:11:14,267 --> 00:11:15,300
And she's ugly!

208
00:11:16,633 --> 00:11:18,033
Hey, Faye's not ugly!

209
00:11:18,500 --> 00:11:20,333
And just because we're not doing
anything here,

210
00:11:20,467 --> 00:11:21,733
it means we're not really doing
anything.

211
00:11:21,867 --> 00:11:22,667
Yeah, right.

212
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:25,867
You know, Vince,
were you a drug addict before?

213
00:11:26,133 --> 00:11:27,467
You look like you're on drugs.

214
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:29,833
- This, maybe, yeah.
- It looks like this.

215
00:11:29,967 --> 00:11:32,200
No, because we just studied
this place.

216
00:11:32,333 --> 00:11:34,333
If there's anyone who will
abduct you,

217
00:11:34,467 --> 00:11:36,167
we'll take care of it.

218
00:11:36,300 --> 00:11:38,067
Well, maybe you don't know us,
man.

219
00:11:38,367 --> 00:11:39,467
Well, there's taho,
why don't you treat me?

220
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,933
Okay, let's go buy some.

221
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:43,400
Mister, do you still have taho?

222
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:44,467
There's none.

223
00:11:44,767 --> 00:11:45,600
Just resting.

224
00:11:46,033 --> 00:11:47,867
Why don't you buy from me,
Lumpia!

225
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:49,433
Taho was what we wanted.

226
00:11:49,567 --> 00:11:50,733
Too bad there's nothing left.

227
00:11:54,733 --> 00:11:55,967
Mister, are you out of taho?

228
00:11:56,867 --> 00:11:57,767
Just lucky.

229
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,000
I hope everyone.

230
00:11:59,467 --> 00:12:00,467
Okay.

231
00:12:03,367 --> 00:12:04,767
We're strong too.

232
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:07,133
Yes, Hey, have a snack!

233
00:12:07,267 --> 00:12:08,167
- It's Abi.
- Mar!

234
00:12:08,300 --> 00:12:11,067
-Oh no, it's going to cost more.
-That's right.

235
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,533
It's been five days, Bi.

236
00:12:12,667 --> 00:12:13,467
Have some snacks.

237
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:14,700
Next time, Abi.

238
00:12:15,067 --> 00:12:17,100
Maybe the Kapitana wants some.
Bobby's there too.

239
00:12:17,233 --> 00:12:18,100
What a shame. Oh my!

240
00:12:18,900 --> 00:12:19,400
I'm hungry.

241
00:12:19,533 --> 00:12:20,433
You look full.

242
00:12:22,233 --> 00:12:25,233
Why is the man still selling?
He ran out of stock a while ago.

243
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:27,067
Yes, he's hard-working.

244
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:29,767
He sells taho in the morning
and balut at night.

245
00:12:30,167 --> 00:12:30,800
Really?

246
00:12:31,267 --> 00:12:31,833
Yes.

247
00:12:31,967 --> 00:12:33,100
He has so many rackets.

248
00:12:33,233 --> 00:12:37,267
But of all the vendors I know,
I've only seen that one now.

249
00:12:37,867 --> 00:12:38,767
I thought he was an outsider.

250
00:12:39,333 --> 00:12:40,100
Outsider?

251
00:12:42,433 --> 00:12:43,800
Hey, Abi.

252
00:12:44,800 --> 00:12:45,933
What do we have here?

253
00:12:46,267 --> 00:12:50,400
Maybe that's the gunman
who was sent to kill us, Abdul.

254
00:12:50,567 --> 00:12:51,533
Yes, yes, well...

255
00:12:51,833 --> 00:12:53,900
Well, Mar, we were identified.

256
00:12:55,733 --> 00:12:56,800
What happened to you?

257
00:12:56,933 --> 00:12:58,767
Why are you looking suspiciously
at the Taho vendor?

258
00:12:58,900 --> 00:13:01,367
Remember,
we recognized Oppa sniper?

259
00:13:01,767 --> 00:13:04,867
Abdul and I are nervous.
Maybe he'll kill us later.

260
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:09,033
Yes, Bobby, and now there's
an outsider selling taho.

261
00:13:09,167 --> 00:13:10,567
Who knows, maybe that's a
suspect.

262
00:13:16,633 --> 00:13:18,367
Bok, let's eat first.

263
00:13:18,767 --> 00:13:19,533
I'm hungry.

264
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:22,300
Are you hungry again?

265
00:13:25,233 --> 00:13:25,933
Wait.

266
00:13:26,833 --> 00:13:27,633
I know this guy.

267
00:13:28,867 --> 00:13:29,700
That's the one I encountered

268
00:13:29,833 --> 00:13:31,367
who attacked Selena
at the safehouse.

269
00:13:31,833 --> 00:13:32,167
Let's go.

270
00:13:34,733 --> 00:13:36,700
Mayor, we'll just call you.

271
00:13:36,833 --> 00:13:38,200
Okay. Thank you very much.

272
00:13:38,333 --> 00:13:39,233
Yes, okay.

273
00:13:42,400 --> 00:13:43,200
- Mira!
- Mayor!

274
00:13:43,733 --> 00:13:44,633
What a pleasant surprise.

275
00:13:44,767 --> 00:13:45,533
Same here.

276
00:13:45,900 --> 00:13:47,367
What are you doing here?

277
00:13:47,500 --> 00:13:51,167
I filed a complaint against,
Victor Santiago.

278
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:54,967
Is this about the exposé
of the gang member, Daga?

279
00:13:55,333 --> 00:13:56,367
Yes.

280
00:13:56,500 --> 00:14:00,067
I haven't thanked you yet.
Thank you very much, Mira.

281
00:14:00,567 --> 00:14:01,533
I'm just doing my job, Mayor.

282
00:14:01,667 --> 00:14:02,300
Me too.

283
00:14:02,433 --> 00:14:04,933
It's about keeping Calabari safe

284
00:14:05,667 --> 00:14:08,633
from the likes
of Victor Santiago.

285
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:11,133
Excuse me, Mayor.
You can go ahead, Mayor.

286
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:12,333
Oh, okay.

287
00:14:12,467 --> 00:14:13,833
- Excuse me.
- Okay.

288
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:19,000
I'm just asking if you see
anything suspicious here.

289
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:21,400
There's nothing.

290
00:14:22,233 --> 00:14:23,333
Are you sure?

291
00:14:23,467 --> 00:14:26,033
Is there anyone passing by
that you're not familiar with?

292
00:14:26,400 --> 00:14:27,067
There's nothing.

293
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,033
Did you see anyone?

294
00:14:35,167 --> 00:14:36,067
Mister, wait a minute!

295
00:14:43,833 --> 00:14:45,333
Ma'am, are you going
to buy something?

296
00:14:47,167 --> 00:14:48,233
I would like to ask something.

297
00:14:51,267 --> 00:14:51,867
Stop!

298
00:14:56,533 --> 00:14:57,200
Stop!

299
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:09,533
What's your problem?

300
00:15:10,900 --> 00:15:12,067
What's in your bag?

301
00:15:12,500 --> 00:15:13,233
Put that down!

302
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,500
What?

303
00:15:14,633 --> 00:15:15,667
I don't understand.

304
00:15:16,067 --> 00:15:17,567
Well, put that bag down!

305
00:15:17,700 --> 00:15:18,500
This?

306
00:15:30,300 --> 00:15:32,367
Go around, I'll follow!

307
00:15:40,033 --> 00:15:45,533
Move! Move!

308
00:15:53,567 --> 00:15:54,533
Where did he go?

309
00:15:54,667 --> 00:15:55,933
- There.
- There.

310
00:15:56,333 --> 00:15:57,500
Go, go, go!

311
00:16:03,567 --> 00:16:04,400
Are you ok?

312
00:16:04,533 --> 00:16:05,300
Yes.

313
00:16:32,333 --> 00:16:33,400
Move! Move!

314
00:16:48,567 --> 00:16:49,533
Out of the way!

315
00:17:48,733 --> 00:17:49,800
Stop!

316
00:17:52,267 --> 00:17:53,667
Hey, stop!

317
00:18:24,067 --> 00:18:25,067
Stop!

318
00:18:54,433 --> 00:18:55,733
Don't try to do something bad.

319
00:18:55,900 --> 00:18:57,267
I'm tired!

320
00:19:26,833 --> 00:19:28,100
Ma'am, have pity on me!

321
00:19:28,733 --> 00:19:29,867
I was just ordered!

322
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,267
And I don't know them, Ma'am.

323
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:33,333
They're just sending me money
and giving me instructions.

324
00:19:33,467 --> 00:19:34,033
That's all.

325
00:19:34,167 --> 00:19:35,867
Let's talk at the precinct!

326
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:31,000
Stop!

327
00:21:56,333 --> 00:21:56,967
Dizon!

328
00:22:52,767 --> 00:22:55,433
Why don't you just die?

329
00:23:01,467 --> 00:23:02,600
Die!

330
00:23:02,733 --> 00:23:04,433
Die!

331
00:23:07,367 --> 00:23:12,033
You challenged the wrong guy
because I don't give up.

332
00:24:02,933 --> 00:24:05,400
Based on the ballistic
examination of the bullet.

333
00:24:05,533 --> 00:24:08,133
It is estimated to have been
in Bullet's head for 10 years.

334
00:24:08,267 --> 00:24:09,700
And according to our database,

335
00:24:09,833 --> 00:24:14,900
it came from a gun registered
in the name of Victor Santiago.

336
00:24:15,033 --> 00:24:16,233
Hey, Sir Tonyo!

337
00:24:16,367 --> 00:24:17,133
Sir Tonyo?

338
00:24:17,267 --> 00:24:18,833
Your neck is long,
is that a giraffe?

339
00:24:18,967 --> 00:24:20,533
Feels good, doesn't it?

340
00:24:20,667 --> 00:24:21,600
Doesn't it?

341
00:24:21,733 --> 00:24:24,200
Especially when your crush
is the action star!

342
00:24:24,333 --> 00:24:26,467
Enriquez, I just thought
it would be better

343
00:24:26,600 --> 00:24:29,800
if you hear what Daga has
to say for transparency.

344
00:24:29,967 --> 00:24:31,867
I don't know what we'll get out
of it,

345
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:34,367
but I hope it helps with the
case we're investigating.

346
00:24:34,667 --> 00:24:36,933
Hey, you guys are the ones.

347
00:24:37,433 --> 00:24:38,100
Which one are we?
